		<!-- message -->
		<div>Did a search and couldn't find one, but I'm looking for a good aggro management guide to post on my guilds message boards.  I'm pretty sick and tired of explaining to people why they shouldn't do this or use that and I'm probably starting to look like a know it all ass, but on raids and exp groups we have a lot of members just clueless about managing their aggro, and these all being 60-65 in lvl, or maybe they've been grouping with knights lately /shrug  Just annoying as all hell when people that have been playing for 3 years still don't get that warrior's rely entirely on procs for aggro, and even when you do proc, you're not going to hold aggro indefinately off a ranger snaring+proccing CoF +nuking +dotting.  Hell, I can even live 3 of those but CoF is just fucking pointless aggro, god I hate sony for giving rangers that buff.<br />
<br />
A link would be much appreciated, otherwise I might have to write something up myself in which case I'll likely get accused of telling people how to play their class.<br />
<br />
Might as well add that I use BoC/SotBS for aggro before anyone asks.</div>
