	<td class="alt2" style="border-right: 1px solid #181B16;"  width="160">
		<div id="postmenu_44888">
				
				moglar
				
			</div>
			
		    <div class="smallfont">Guest</div>
			
		
			
			
					<div class="smallfont">
				&nbsp;<br />
				<div class="info"> </div>
				
				
				
				
				
				 
				<div class="info">Posts: n/a 
				</div>
				<div class="info">   </div>
				</div>														
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>Here's a quick and dirty one</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#131619" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Just typed this up in 5 mins, tell me what you think.<br />
<br />
<br />
Aggro Management Guide, By Moglar Moregoth, Troll warrior of bristlebane<br />
<br />
1.)	Don’t mash you’re taunt key every time it refreshes.  Instead, wait for the mob to turn from you, to another player, THEN hit taunt.  Many people do not understand that taunt bumps you to the top of the mobs hate list, then adds only one hate point.  So, if you are already at the top of the mob’s hate list and hit taunt, you gain a mere 1 point of hate.<br />
<br />
Say, for example, you’ve got the mob’s attention and you hit taunt cause you feel like it.  Just so happens that the mage nukes the paste out of the mob the second after you hit taunt, thereby ganking you’re agro.  Now you’ve got to wait until taunt refreshes before you can use the button for it’s intended purpose.  The mage will take a round of melee, which could kill him depending on the mob.  Well, if you’re taunt fails, you’re looking at 2 or 3 rounds of melee possible on the mage b4 you can hit taunt.<br />
<br />
Bottom line is that it’s more efficient to hit taunt only when you loose agro.<br />
2.)	/shield the person that stole your agro.  Sometimes I get agro back just form the sheer act of /shielding the mob’s target.  Assist the mob and hit shield.<br />
3.)	If those don’t work, use that area taunt button ONLY if the mob’s target is at or above 2 bubs of health.<br />
4.)	CONTROVERSIAL? – a LOT of times, when taunt fails at first, I’ll sit/stand/attack and the mob will switch back to me before taunt refreshes, simply based on a touch of sit agro.  I don’t have any numbers or testing to back this up, but it works so well for me that I live by it.  I won’t /shield a target before I try the sit/stand/attack again, because sitting will cancel your /shielding.<br />
5.)	Most importantly, weapons.  Sure, DPS is important I guess, but high agro procs like (stuns) are the bomb.  Get the greatstaff of thunder or the copper hammer of striking/bloodsworn combo.  A few procs per fight mean a world of difference.<br />
6.)    Establish agro before anyone else engages.  It’s a delicate matter to insist, to a pickup group, that they give you 8 to 12 seconds of whacking on the mob praying for a proc before they start casting and melee; however it’s important and greatly reduces the chance of loosing control of the mob.  You loose you’re agro for any signifigant portion of the fight, and the entire efficiency of the group is reduced.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt2" style="border-right: 1px solid #181B16;">
		
		
		
		
