		<!-- message -->
		<div>I was actually looking for a guide on what everyone except the MT should be doing to avoid aggro, though I appreciate your input Mog.<br />
<br />
Such as the ranger self only buff Call of Fire (65dd 0sec stun)  I fail to see any use for this in exp groups or on raids with 2 exceptions.  1) If the ranger is the MT 2) If caster interupts are absolutely essential.  Other than that, this buff, while adding very little dps to the ranger, does much more harm than good.  Example, if you have a rogue in the group and the ranger is positioned on the side of the mob, procs CoF, draws aggro, rogue misses bs dps, cleric wastes mana on ranger, and on top of that the rangers dps actually goes down since the mob is now facing him and parrying,riposting,dodging etc. <br />
<br />
A guide with tips like this for other classes would make my life so much easier as a war.</div>
