	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Time is the best answer to aggro problems, for tanks and other members.  As the tank, it is imperative that you jump on the mob as quickly as possible.  Even one or two rounds can be a huge advantage in initial aggro while you're waiting on a proc.<br />
<br />
Likewise, if someone is drawing aggro, usually the best thing they can do is wait a few seconds before engaging/casting.<br />
<br />
Use paladins to your advantage.  For example, lets say you wake a mob, taunt having failed, and it's whacking the enchanter.  A good paladin (or cleric) can stun the mob for many seconds, accomplishing two things: 1) it protects the ench and 2) it generates higher over-all aggro and you'll have one or two more chances to get a successful taunt in, stealing that aggro, before the mob can do much damage.  Of course, this tactic assumes you can out-aggro the paladin's straight melee.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
