		<!-- message -->
		<div>It's all good, except on Mog's post...2 things.<br />
<br />
First:<br />
Taunt is (Hate_of_most_hated_player + 1) <b>+</b> (Hate_bonus)<br />
Hate_bonus is a combination of things like proximity, whether or not mob is snared, whether or not you're sitting or /shielding <font size="1">(I beleive /shield gives a boost in aggro, that alone gets mobs to turn for me. On a related note, /assisting mobs seems to piss them off too, sometimes when I type /as to get my shield target, that makes them turn)</font><br />
<br />
Second:<br />
8-12 sec solo tank on EXP mobs is too much.<br />
When the puller pulls, pump arrows into the mob. When the puller runs by you, run up and attack/disarm/taunt to make sure you get the mobs attention. Doing this gives you quite a bit of aggro. <br />
Don't worry about &quot;wasting&quot; Taunt now.. any slower who slows within the first 6 seconds of a mobs life is asking to be dead. In reality, slow takes a few secs to cast and you will have plenty of time to refresh.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
