Uh... no. I'm sorry, I've been in guilds where I was the main tank on certain raids. Yes sometimes I would lose aggro to an overnuker. And I'd send them a tell &quot;Wtb aggro off your overnuking&quot; or &quot;Wts you a FAQ on not overnuking&quot; or sometime just a simple &quot;You're over nuking, please control your aggro&quot;<br />
<br />
After this being said I'd sometime get a tell from an officer or guildleader saying &quot;X caster says you're trying to tell them how to play their class.  X caster says they'll guild remove if you're not put back in your place.&quot;<br />
<br />
Warriors are so easy to replace it's disgusting. Most high end guilds -will not- take warrior unless they meet insane requirements. Such as level 65, Maxed Defensive AND offensive AA, elemental or time flags, all keys, and the like. Whereas the same guilds take the time to go back and flag a level 62 cleric or wizard recruit with under 30 AA all the way through time.<br />
<br />
So I feel that this isn't a solution unless you are the guild leader or an officer with power. If you've experienced different, that's great but I've really been forced to keep my mouth shut when it comes to explaining to a caster that things should be done a certain way.</div>
